description: Management Professional) certification from the PMI® (Project Management Institute), updated to the 6th edition of the PMBoK® (Project Management Body of Knowledge) released in 2018. The Project Management Institute a leading certification for individuals working in the project management environment and in the 6th edition of the PMBoK sees the consideration of both Agile and waterfall approaches to project management. The PMP® certification combines breadth of knowledge with extensive pre-requisites to ensure that candidates who successfully complete the exam are  well versed in the various tools and techniques used by successful project managers. The qualification is targeted at individuals with over five years of experience working as a project manager and seeking to validate their knowledge and experience through becoming certified. Don’t despair if you don’t have five years experience as our series will also prepare you for the Certified Associate of Project Management (CAPM®) certification which is available for those just embarking on a career in project management.  PMP® and CAPM® are registered trademarks of the Project Management Institute.

episodes.title: Overview
episodes.transcript:
WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.072 --> 00:00:05.978
[MUSIC]

2
00:00:05.978 --> 00:00:13.295
Hi and welcome to your PMI, PMP 6 series.

3
00:00:13.295 --> 00:00:15.155
What does that mean,
all of those acronyms, right?

4
00:00:15.155 --> 00:00:19.465
It's the Project Management Institute,
the sixth edition

5
00:00:19.465 --> 00:00:23.705
of the Project Management body
of knowledge, or the PMBOK.

6
00:00:23.705 --> 00:00:26.865
And the certification that we're
actually going to be covering

7
00:00:26.865 --> 00:00:29.695
is the project management professional.

8
00:00:29.695 --> 00:00:33.125
Now, in our title on the bottom,

9
00:00:33.125 --> 00:00:37.830
we will call that just PMP,
and we'll call it PMP6.

10
00:00:37.830 --> 00:00:39.410
So we have in brackets or

11
00:00:39.410 --> 00:00:44.950
parentheses 2018 because this is when
the update was released, in 2018.

12
00:00:44.950 --> 00:00:49.830
So I'm your subject matter expert, I'm Jo
Peacock, and I'm gonna be with you for

13
00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:51.870
this entire series.

14
00:00:51.870 --> 00:00:56.190
And during this series,
we're going to be taking a walk through

15
00:00:56.190 --> 00:00:59.400
the project management body of knowledge.

16
00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:01.390
That's a book,
I've already mentioned that.

17
00:01:01.390 --> 00:01:04.520
It's quite a large book as well,
that's this book here.

18
00:01:04.520 --> 00:01:06.360
And we're going to be
walking through that.

19
00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:10.150
And we're going to be looking
at the concepts of a project,

20
00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:13.960
what a project means,
the temporary nature of a project.

21
00:01:13.960 --> 00:01:18.690
And then we're going to be looking at all
of the processes that we have to undertake

22
00:01:18.690 --> 00:01:21.080
when we are managing a project.

23
00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:25.650
So we'll be looking at the project
from the inception and

24
00:01:25.650 --> 00:01:30.130
the idea, right the way through to
the design and the development, and

25
00:01:30.130 --> 00:01:35.460
then the release and deployment of
a product into a live environment.

26
00:01:35.460 --> 00:01:40.775
Now, whilst we are here at ITProTV,
and obviously we have a focus on IT,

27
00:01:40.775 --> 00:01:44.524
the simple fact is that
the project management body

28
00:01:44.524 --> 00:01:49.166
of knowledge does not necessarily
have a complete focus on IT.

29
00:01:49.166 --> 00:01:55.185
So we will be looking at this from the
perspective of general project management,

30
00:01:55.185 --> 00:01:59.646
although we will be obviously
bringing in some IT elements.

31
00:01:59.646 --> 00:02:00.217
But as I said,

32
00:02:00.217 --> 00:02:03.659
we're gonna be looking at this from the
perspective of general project management.

33
00:02:03.659 --> 00:02:09.100
So join with us,
you're gonna have a great show.

34
00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:12.100
You're gonna learn a lot
about project management.

35
00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:13.080
It's gonna prepare you for

36
00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:19.440
the project management professional
examination at the end of the series.

37
00:02:19.440 --> 00:02:23.090
So join us in our series on

38
00:02:23.090 --> 00:02:27.640
project management professionals from
the PMI, the Project Management Institute.

39
00:02:27.640 --> 00:02:31.480
And it's the sixth edition
which was released in 2018.

40
00:02:31.480 --> 00:02:33.780
So I will see you on our next show.

41
00:02:33.780 --> 00:02:40.309
[MUSIC]
